The paper presents a generic framework for speeding up machine learning algorithms with structured random matrices, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses applications such as LSH-based algorithms (cs.DS), kernel computations (cs.IT), convex optimization (cs.CV), and quantization (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CV, and cs.AI.
